        "content": "<p>Hi! I'm working on formalizing some games on graphs on the side and was wondering if there is a computable way of getting the cardinality of a vertex set of <code>SimpleGraph.Finsubgraph (completeGraph V)</code>, suppose that we have <code>[Fintype V] [DecidableEq V]</code>. Right now I do <code>graph.property.toFinset.card</code> but that requires to mark everything that uses that instance as <code>noncomputable</code> which renders it quite useless actually.</p>",
